{
  "texts": [
    "For each class of CRC, FN is the entire sum of CRC images that are not classified as this CRC class.",
    "The hyper-parameters used are the minibatch size which is the amount of data included in each sub-epoch weight change and is chosen to be 10.",
    "Using small batch sizes usually achieves the best generalization performance.",
    "The learning rate determines the step size at each iteration while moving towards a minimum of a loss function.",
    "In my experiments, the learning rate was chosen to be 0.0001."
  ]
}